#. HTML: <section class="sutta" id="an4.90"><article><div class="hgroup"><p class="division">
msgctxt "an4.90:0.1"
msgid "Aṅguttara Nikāya 4 "
msgstr "Numbered Discourses 4 "

#. HTML: </p><p>
msgctxt "an4.90:0.2"
msgid "9. Macalavagga "
msgstr "9. Confirmed "

#. HTML: </p><h1>
#. VAR: samaṇamacala-khandhasuttaṃ (bj)
msgctxt "an4.90:0.3"
msgid "90. Khandhasutta "
msgstr "90. Aggregates "

#. HTML: </h1></div><p>
#. REF: sc1
msgctxt "an4.90:1.1"
msgid "“Cattārome, bhikkhave, puggalā santo saṃvijjamānā lokasmiṃ. "
msgstr "“Mendicants, these four people are found in the world. "

msgctxt "an4.90:1.2"
msgid "Katame cattāro? "
msgstr "What four? "

msgctxt "an4.90:1.3"
msgid "Samaṇamacalo, samaṇapuṇḍarīko, samaṇapadumo, samaṇesu samaṇasukhumālo. "
msgstr "The confirmed ascetic, the white lotus ascetic, the pink lotus ascetic, and the exquisite ascetic of ascetics. "

#. HTML: </p><p>
#. REF: sc2
msgctxt "an4.90:2.1"
msgid "Kathañca, bhikkhave, puggalo samaṇamacalo hoti? "
msgstr "And how is a person a confirmed ascetic? "

msgctxt "an4.90:2.2"
msgid "Idha, bhikkhave, bhikkhu sekho hoti appattamānaso, anuttaraṃ yogakkhemaṃ patthayamāno viharati. "
msgstr "It’s when a mendicant is a trainee who hasn’t achieved their heart’s desire, but lives aspiring to the supreme sanctuary. "

msgctxt "an4.90:2.3"
msgid "Evaṃ kho, bhikkhave, puggalo samaṇamacalo hoti. "
msgstr "That’s how a person is a confirmed ascetic. "

#. HTML: </p><p>
#. REF: sc3
msgctxt "an4.90:3.1"
msgid "Kathañca, bhikkhave, puggalo samaṇapuṇḍarīko hoti? "
msgstr "And how is a person a white lotus ascetic? "

msgctxt "an4.90:3.2"
msgid "Idha, bhikkhave, bhikkhu pañcasu upādānakkhandhesu udayabbayānupassī viharati: "
msgstr "It’s when a mendicant meditates observing rise and fall in the five grasping aggregates. "

msgctxt "an4.90:3.3"
msgid "‘iti rūpaṃ, iti rūpassa samudayo, iti rūpassa atthaṅgamo; "
msgstr "‘Such is form, such is the origin of form, such is the ending of form. "

msgctxt "an4.90:3.4"
msgid "iti vedanā … pe … "
msgstr "Such is feeling … "

msgctxt "an4.90:3.5"
msgid "iti saññā … pe … "
msgstr "Such is perception … "

msgctxt "an4.90:3.6"
msgid "iti saṅkhārā … pe … "
msgstr "Such are choices … "

msgctxt "an4.90:3.7"
msgid "iti viññāṇaṃ, iti viññāṇassa samudayo, iti viññāṇassa atthaṅgamo’ti; "
msgstr "Such is consciousness, such is the origin of consciousness, such is the ending of consciousness.’ "

msgctxt "an4.90:3.8"
msgid "no ca kho aṭṭha vimokkhe kāyena phusitvā viharati. "
msgstr "But they don’t have direct meditative experience of the eight liberations. "

msgctxt "an4.90:3.9"
msgid "Evaṃ kho, bhikkhave, puggalo samaṇapuṇḍarīko hoti. "
msgstr "That’s how a person is a white lotus ascetic. "

#. HTML: </p><p>
#. REF: pts-vp-pli2.91, sc4
msgctxt "an4.90:4.1"
msgid "Kathañca, bhikkhave, puggalo samaṇapadumo hoti? "
msgstr "And how is a person a pink lotus ascetic? "

msgctxt "an4.90:4.2"
msgid "Idha, bhikkhave, bhikkhu pañcasu upādānakkhandhesu udayabbayānupassī viharati: "
msgstr "It’s when a mendicant meditates observing rise and fall in the five grasping aggregates. "

msgctxt "an4.90:4.3"
msgid "‘iti rūpaṃ, iti rūpassa samudayo, iti rūpassa atthaṅgamo; "
msgstr "‘Such is form, such is the origin of form, such is the ending of form. "

msgctxt "an4.90:4.4"
msgid "iti vedanā … pe … "
msgstr "Such is feeling … "

msgctxt "an4.90:4.5"
msgid "iti saññā … pe … "
msgstr "Such is perception … "

msgctxt "an4.90:4.6"
msgid "iti saṅkhārā … pe … "
msgstr "Such are choices … "

msgctxt "an4.90:4.7"
msgid "iti viññāṇaṃ, iti viññāṇassa samudayo, iti viññāṇassa atthaṅgamo’ti; "
msgstr "Such is consciousness, such is the origin of consciousness, such is the ending of consciousness.’ "

msgctxt "an4.90:4.8"
msgid "aṭṭha ca vimokkhe kāyena phusitvā viharati. "
msgstr "And they have direct meditative experience of the eight liberations. "

msgctxt "an4.90:4.9"
msgid "Evaṃ kho, bhikkhave, puggalo samaṇapadumo hoti. "
msgstr "That’s how a person is a pink lotus ascetic. "

#. HTML: </p><p>
#. REF: sc5
msgctxt "an4.90:5.1"
msgid "Kathañca, bhikkhave, puggalo samaṇesu samaṇasukhumālo hoti? "
msgstr "And how is a person an exquisite ascetic of ascetics? "

msgctxt "an4.90:5.2"
msgid "Idha, bhikkhave, bhikkhu yācitova bahulaṃ cīvaraṃ paribhuñjati, appaṃ ayācito … pe … mameva taṃ, bhikkhave, sammā vadamāno vadeyya samaṇesu samaṇasukhumāloti. "
msgstr "It’s when a mendicant usually uses only what they’ve been invited to accept … And if anyone should be rightly called an exquisite ascetic of ascetics, it’s me. "

#. HTML: </p><p>
msgctxt "an4.90:5.3"
msgid "Ime kho, bhikkhave, cattāro puggalā santo saṃvijjamānā lokasmin”ti. "
msgstr "These are the four people found in the world.” "

#. HTML: </p><p class="endsection">
msgctxt "an4.90:5.4"
msgid "Dasamaṃ. "
msgstr " "

#. HTML: </p><p class="endsection">
msgctxt "an4.90:5.5"
msgid "Macalavaggo catuttho. "
msgstr " "

#. HTML: </p><blockquote class="uddanagatha"><p>
#. REF: sc6
msgctxt "an4.90:6.1"
msgid "Pāṇātipāto ca musā, "
msgstr " "

#. HTML: <br>
msgctxt "an4.90:6.2"
msgid "avaṇṇakodhatamoṇatā; "
msgstr " "

#. HTML: <br>
msgctxt "an4.90:6.3"
msgid "Putto saṃyojanañceva, "
msgstr " "

#. HTML: <br>
msgctxt "an4.90:6.4"
msgid "diṭṭhi khandhena te dasāti. "
msgstr ""

#. HTML: </p></blockquote></article></section></body></html>
